    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.8.0-dev+519-g6f6286e4f9\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 8.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux 5.15.19-1-MANJARO\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.10.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:set mouse=a\r\nisome text <C-o>V\r\n```\r\nright click visually selected area.\r\nleft click on `cut`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither:\r\nText being cut\r\nOr:\r\nThere being no popup menu\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nAn error is raised:\r\n`E335: Menu not defined for Insert mode`",
